        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-04-20 06:26:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nHi and thanks for the proposal,\ntwo important things:\n* first, we must not retrieve stuff from Internet at boot of the components. So sql files must be retrieved and put into the chart\n* please use common templates and pattern for mariadb service: some people prefer to have local databases while other prefers to have a global one.\n  Here, but I may be wrong, it seems that we must use the shared one. VID is a good example I think to see how to handle both cases (https://github.com/onap/oom/tree/master/kubernetes/vid)\n  @Andreas, do you have another component that works well for your case (a DB per component)?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c2a085c33934fdb0047a647cd10f504c25c30e1a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5315,
          "name": "Mahmoud Abdelhamid",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mahmoud.abdelhamid@orange.com",
          "username": "mhamid"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-04-20 10:37:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHello Sylvain,\nRegarding the first point:\n> * first, we must not retrieve stuff from Internet at boot of the components. So sql files must be retrieved and put into the chart\n\nThat was the original solution, but when we uploaded all needed SQL files into OOM, the chart size became more than (1M) causing the helm deploy to fail. That is why we used online fetching instead. Putting all files into tar file didn't help much as still the size more than 1M. I will try another solution.\n\n> * please use common templates and pattern for mariadb service: some people prefer to have local databases while other prefers to have a global one.\n\nLet me review this making sure it is correct.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
